# Methodology notes
- downloaded Annual Reports available on tribunalsontario.ca, printing to PDF the sections that pertain to the Landlord and Tenant board
- found reports unavailable through the above website on archive.org by accessing archived pages of ltb.on.ca and downloading the reports

- built a spreadsheet of data available in the reports by hand, copy-pasting information from the reports (yes.)
	- took notes on the operational changes over time, organisations consulted, changes in metrics reported etc.

- used `tesseract 5.3.4` and `ocrmypdf 15.2.0+dfsg1` to OCR the report contents, then `qpdf` to merge all reports into one document

- started creating a metrics dictionary for the various data points found in the reports
- used python to change the way the data is displayed in the "notes" spreadsheet into the more standard long format, with the metric_ids from the dictionary

- built `operational_metrics.csv` with data extracted from reports - correctness of data is not validated
- built `regional_metrics.csv` with data extracted from reports - correctness of data is not validated
- built `financial_metrics.csv` with data extracted from reports - correctness of data is not validated, additional data may be available in other government Open Data repositories

## Staffing metrics extraction method

1998-2010 staffing data was extracted based on the biographies of members included at the end of the reports from those years.

1. Sections of reports with biographies were extracted `pdftotext -f STARTPAGE -l ENDPAGE INPUT.pdf OUTPUT.txt`
2. AI-assisted counting was attempted and proved unreliable when compared to hand counting
3. Extracted probable biography headings with `extract_names.py` (898 candidate lines, "heuristic-based pattern matching")
4. Deduped list with `dedupe_names.py`, built a list of canonical names and their variants by hand from the deduped list of names
5. Counted the number of times canonical names appear in the report extracts from 1. and how many names appear with ("Part time") or some variant immediately after them with `count_members.py`, output is `member_counts_by_file.csv`
6. Added the above to `staffing_metrics.csv` for the years where member biographies were included in the report.

From 2020 onwards, adjudicator numbers were reported directly. The number of mediators or "Dispute Resolution Offcers" has not been reported to date.










